column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Partly cloudy- 5-8 mph winds- light waves- in 80'sf all week- now 48 F at night and 70 F days
Sunny- 80 F- a lot of pollen on top of lake- shoreline white- cottony bloom in weed beds
Hot days and nights- weeds falling to bottom- mucky bottom- clear- nice day.
Beautiful-sunny day- some pollen in the lake.
Weeds to top of water- temp of lake has dropped 20 degrees since the beginning of June.
Water temp is 68 degrees- cool for this time of year.
The temperature is 75 degrees and there are clouds.
The temperature is 52 degrees- foliage off trees- clear sky- and very few weeds visible.
Partly cloudy- 2" of rain in last 48 hours- lots of pollen.
Gorgeous day.  Had boat races on the lake 8/7/93.  Some weeds floating but not too bad a disturbance.
Windy- clear skies- 66 degrees- algae bloom 2 weeks ago today- clear water.
Blue sky- few clouds- 60 degrees day.
Great day- sunny and nice- weeds are at top of the lake- must be at least 9-10' tall and are growing
Ice off 5/13/96- very late.  Had a lot of fish kill this winter.
Water is not clear-blue as usual.  Lots of dead weeds decaying fish from winter kill.  Water has an odor.  Old brown muck and decay on anchor.
Green plants on the anchor for the first time this year.
First time all summer- clear-blue water.
Ice off May 1- 1997.  Ducks and loons returned.  Did have green plants on anchor.
Ice out 4/10/98.  Lake did okay for oxygen.
Warm.  Lots of swimmers.  No problems.
Ice out 4/13. large clumps of vegetation from bottom are loosened. pollen floating on surface.
Vegetation tips out of water by June 10.  Lots of rain.
Pollen blossoming but quite clear.  Beach closed - high bacteria count.
Lots of vegetation in the lake + loons on the lake.
